Step 1: Calculate the Debt to Equity Ratio.  
• From the balance sheet, Total Current Liabilities = 2,736,025.72 and Total Owner's Equity = 11,330,150.23.  
• Debt to Equity Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Owner’s Equity = 2,736,025.72 / 11,330,150.23 ≈ 0.2415  
• Rounded to two decimals, this ratio is 0.24.  

Step 2: Calculate the Net Profit Margin.  
• From the income statement, Net Profit = –1,669,849.77 and Total Revenue = 6,920,513.79.  
• Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100% = (–1,669,849.77 / 6,920,513.79) × 100 ≈ –24.14%  

Step 3: Calculate the Operating Cash Flow to Current Liabilities Ratio.  
• From the cash flow statement, Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = –5,714,107.45 and Total Current Liabilities (from the balance sheet) = 2,736,025.72.  
• Operating CF to Current Liabilities Ratio = –5,714,107.45 / 2,736,025.72 ≈ –2.087  
• Rounded to two decimals, this ratio is –2.09.  

Thus, the solution in the required JSON format is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Debt to Equity Ratio": "0.24",
    "Net Profit Margin": "-24.14%",
    "operating cash flow to current liabilities ratio": "-2.09"
  }
}
